<h1>Introduction to JavaScript</h1>
<p>Let's explore a few functionalities of JavaScript.</p>

<h2>Modifying HTML Content with JavaScript</h2>
<p>JavaScript can utilize the HTML method <code>getElementById()</code> to identify and alter content in HTML. See the example below where JavaScript changes the content of an HTML element with id="demo" to "Hello JavaScript":</p>
<pre><code>
 document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello JavaScript";
 </code></pre>
 <p>Here, JavaScript recognizes both single and double quotes:</p>
 <pre><code>
 document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML = 'Hello JavaScript';
 </code></pre>

<h2>Changing HTML Attribute Values</h2>
<p>JavaScript can amend the value of an attribute. For instance, it can change the 'src' attribute of an <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> tag.</p>

<h2>Modifying HTML Styles (CSS)</h2>
<p>JavaScript can also modify an HTML element's style:</p>
<pre><code>
 document.getElementById("demo").style.fontSize = "35px";
</code></pre>

<h2>Hiding and Displaying HTML Elements</h2>
<p>JavaScript can make an HTML element invisible or visible by changing its display style:</p>
<pre><code>
// To hide
 document.getElementById("demo").style.display = "none";

// To show
 document.getElementById("demo").style.display = "block";
</code></pre>

<h2>Fun Facts About JavaScript</h2>
<ul>
<li>JavaScript and Java are different in terms of design and concept.</li>
<li>Brendan Eich invented JavaScript in 1995 and it became an ECMA standard in 1997.</li>
<li>ECMAScript is the official name of the language and ECMA-262 is the standard's official name.</li>
</ul>
